---
description: Core project identity, naming conventions, and cross-cutting rules for Project Codex. Apply to every file in the repo.
globs: ["**/*"]
alwaysApply: true
---
Project Codex — Core Rules
Project Identity

Name: Project Codex — a personal "Life OS" dashboard
Purpose: Daily Briefing + Kanban Task Manager + Canvas Workspace + Interstitial Diary + AI Planning
Single user, self-hosted on shared PHP hosting + SQLite

Stack at a Glance

Backend: PHP 8.2+, PDO/SQLite, no framework
Frontend: React 18, Vite, TypeScript (strict), Tailwind CSS v3
State: TanStack Query v5 (server state) + Zustand v5 (UI state)
Native: Capacitor v6 (mobile) + Tauri v2 (desktop)
AI: Anthropic API (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)

Universal Naming Conventions

Database columns and PHP variables: snake_case
TypeScript types, interfaces, React components: PascalCase
TypeScript variables, functions, hooks: camelCase
API route segments: kebab-case (/api/diary-logs, not /api/diary_logs)
File names — PHP: PascalCase.php; TS/TSX: PascalCase.tsx for components, camelCase.ts for utils/hooks
CSS classes: Tailwind utility classes only — no custom CSS classes except in tailwind.config.ts theme extension

Timestamps

All timestamps stored as Unix integers (seconds) in SQLite
PHP: use time() for current timestamp; never date() for storage
TypeScript: type alias UnixTimestamp = number; convert to Date only for display
All display formatting uses date-fns — never new Date().toLocaleString()

Soft Deletes

Goals, Projects, Tasks, Notes, DiaryLogs: never hard delete
Set deleted_at = unixepoch() instead
Every query MUST include WHERE deleted_at IS NULL unless explicitly fetching archived/trash items
PHP repositories expose a restore(int $id) method that sets deleted_at = NULL

Error Handling

PHP: all exceptions caught at the front controller; return ApiError JSON envelope; never expose stack traces
TypeScript: all API calls check response.success before accessing .data
No console.log in committed code — use console.error only for genuine errors
User-facing errors shown via the toast system (uiStore.addToast()), never alert()

Security

API protected by X-Codex-Key header middleware on every non-public endpoint
API key stored in backend .env, never in frontend source or git
Frontend reads API key from VITE_API_KEY env var (Vite strips it at build time for native targets)
SQLite file location: backend/database/codex.sqlite — outside public/ webroot
All PDO queries use prepared statements — no string interpolation in SQL ever
OAuth tokens stored in integration_tokens table — never in localStorage or cookies

Git Hygiene

Never commit .env, *.sqlite, *.sqlite-wal, *.sqlite-shm, node_modules/, vendor/
.cursorrules and .cursor/ ARE committed — they are project configuration

---
description: PHP backend rules — architecture, patterns, and coding standards for the REST API layer.
globs: ["backend/**/*.php"]
alwaysApply: false
---
Backend PHP Rules
Architecture Pattern
Strict three-layer separation — never skip layers:
Request → Router → Middleware → Controller → Repository → Database
                                           → Service (external APIs)

Controllers: validate input, call repository/service, return response. No SQL. No business logic.
Repositories: all SQL lives here. No HTTP logic. Return plain arrays or null.
Services: external API calls (Anthropic, Google, OpenWeather). No SQL. No HTTP response logic.
Core classes: Router, Request, Response, Database, Middleware — no feature logic.

Database.php — PDO Singleton
php// Always bootstrap with these pragmas on every connection
$pdo->exec('PRAGMA journal_mode = WAL');
$pdo->exec('PRAGMA foreign_keys = ON');
$pdo->exec('PRAGMA synchronous = NORMAL');
$pdo->setAttribute(PDO::ATTR_ERRMODE, PDO::ERRMODE_EXCEPTION);
$pdo->setAttribute(PDO::ATTR_DEFAULT_FETCH_MODE, PDO::FETCH_ASSOC);
Repository Conventions
Every repository must implement these base methods:

findAll(array $filters = [], int $page = 1, int $perPage = 50): array
findById(int $id): ?array
create(array $data): int — returns new row ID
update(int $id, array $data): bool
delete(int $id): bool — soft delete (sets deleted_at)
restore(int $id): bool

Filters array maps to WHERE clauses. Example:
php// TaskRepository::findAll(['project_id' => 3, 'status' => 'in_progress'])
// becomes: WHERE project_id = ? AND status = ? AND deleted_at IS NULL
Always build WHERE clauses dynamically from the filters array — never with string concatenation.
Boolean Casting
SQLite stores booleans as 0|1. Always cast before JSON encoding:
php// In repository, before returning:
$row['canvas_pinned'] = (bool) $row['canvas_pinned'];
$row['is_pinned'] = (bool) $row['is_pinned'];
$row['is_all_day'] = (bool) $row['is_all_day'];
Define a castRow(array $row): array method in each repository listing all boolean fields.
JSON Column Handling
Columns storing JSON (tasks_snapshot, logs_snapshot, parsed_schedule, etc.):
php// On read: always decode
$row['tasks_snapshot'] = json_decode($row['tasks_snapshot'] ?? '[]', true);
// On write: always encode
$data['tasks_snapshot'] = json_encode($data['tasks_snapshot'] ?? []);
Response Envelope
All responses use Response::json() which wraps in the standard envelope:
php// Success
Response::json(['data' => $result]);
// Success with pagination
Response::paginated($items, $total, $page, $perPage);
// Error
Response::error('NOT_FOUND', 'Task not found', 404);
Response::error('VALIDATION_ERROR', 'Title is required', 422, 'title');
Never echo JSON directly. Never die() with JSON.
Transactions
Any endpoint that writes to multiple tables must use a transaction:
php$db->beginTransaction();
try {
    // ... multiple writes
    $db->commit();
} catch (\Exception $e) {
    $db->rollBack();
    Response::error('DB_ERROR', 'Write failed', 500);
}
display_order — Fractional Indexing
When inserting a task at a Kanban position, calculate fractional order:

Inserting at end: max(display_order) + 1.0
Inserting between A and B: (A.display_order + B.display_order) / 2
If gap < 0.001, renumber the entire column: 1.0, 2.0, 3.0, ...

Input Validation
Validate in controller before calling repository. Required pattern:
php$title = trim($request->getBody()['title'] ?? '');
if (empty($title)) {
    Response::error('VALIDATION_ERROR', 'Title is required', 422, 'title');
    return;
}
Validate enums against allowlists — never trust raw input for status, priority, log_type, etc.
CORS Headers
Set in index.php front controller for every request:
phpheader('Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *');
header('Access-Control-Allow-Methods: GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE, OPTIONS');
header('Access-Control-Allow-Headers: Content-Type, X-Codex-Key');
if ($_SERVER['REQUEST_METHOD'] === 'OPTIONS') { http_response_code(204); exit; }
PHP Version & Features

Minimum PHP 8.2 — use named arguments, match expressions, readonly properties, fibers if needed
Use declare(strict_types=1) at the top of every file
Type hint all method parameters and return types
Use ?Type for nullable, never mixed unless unavoidable

---
description: React + TypeScript + Tailwind rules for the Project Codex frontend.
globs: ["frontend/src/**/.{ts,tsx}", "frontend/.{ts,json}"]
alwaysApply: false
---
Frontend React Rules
TypeScript Strictness

tsconfig.json must have "strict": true — no exceptions
No any types — ever. Use unknown and narrow, or define a proper interface
All component props must be explicitly typed interfaces, not inline { prop: type }
Prefer interface over type for object shapes; use type for unions and aliases
All imports from '../types' — never redefine types locally that exist in types/index.ts

Component Structure
Every component file follows this order:
tsx// 1. Imports (external libs → internal components → hooks → types → utils)
// 2. Local types/interfaces (only if component-specific)
// 3. Component function (named export, not default for most)
// 4. Sub-components (if small and tightly coupled)
// 5. Default export at bottom
Use named exports for all components. Default export only for page-level components and lazy-loaded routes.
TanStack Query Conventions
Query key factory pattern — define in api/queryKeys.ts:
tsexport const queryKeys = {
  goals: () => ['goals'] as const,
  goal: (id: number) => ['goals', id] as const,
  tasks: (filters?: TaskFilters) => ['tasks', filters] as const,
  briefing: (date: string) => ['briefing', date] as const,
}

staleTime: goals/projects = 5 minutes, tasks = 2 minutes, briefing = 5 minutes, diary = 30 seconds
gcTime: 10 minutes for all
Mutations must invalidateQueries on success — never manually update cache except for optimistic updates
Optimistic updates only for: QuickLogBar submissions, Kanban drag-drop reorders, task checkbox toggles

Zustand Store Rules
Two stores only:

uiStore: active tab, open modal IDs, toast queue, drawer state, sidebar collapsed
canvasStore: viewport {x, y, zoom}, selected item IDs, drag state

Never put server data in Zustand — that belongs in TanStack Query cache.
Store shape must be typed with an explicit interface:
tsinterface UiStore {
  activeTab: TabId
  openModalId: string | null
  // ...
  setActiveTab: (tab: TabId) => void
  openModal: (id: string) => void
}
Tailwind Rules

Dark mode only for initial build — add dark class to <html> in index.html
Custom semantic colors defined in tailwind.config.ts under theme.extend.colors:

ts  'codex-bg': '#0f0f11',        // page background
  'codex-surface': '#1a1a1f',   // card background
  'codex-border': '#2a2a30',    // border color
  'codex-accent': '#6366f1',    // primary accent (indigo)
  'codex-muted': '#71717a',     // muted text

Use these semantic tokens, not raw Tailwind grays/indigos, for structural UI elements
Mobile-first: write base classes for mobile, md: for tablet, lg: for desktop
No inline styles except for dynamic values (canvas positions, user-defined colors)
No style={{ color: '...' }} for static colors — always a Tailwind class

Component-Specific Rules
KanbanBoard

Use @dnd-kit/core DndContext + @dnd-kit/sortable SortableContext per column
onDragEnd handler calls PATCH /api/tasks/reorder with fractional display_order
Wrap in React.memo — re-renders only when task list for that column changes
Column task lists derived via useMemo from the full tasks query

CanvasWorkspace

Transform state (x, y, zoom) lives in canvasStore — not component state
Pan via pointermove while pointerdown (not mouse events — supports touch)
Zoom via wheel event — clamp between 0.25 and 3.0
Sticky note positions updated optimistically on drag end, then synced via PATCH /api/tasks/:id/canvas
z-index managed in canvasStore — clicking a note brings it to front

QuickLogBar

Controlled input — useState for text, log type, linked project/task
On submit: optimistic update to diary query cache, then POST, then invalidate
Clear and refocus input immediately after submit (don't wait for server)
Keyboard: Enter submits, Escape clears, @ triggers project/task mention picker

Forms & Drawers

No <form> elements — use div with onClick handlers
TaskDrawer: slide up from bottom on mobile (translate-y transition), right panel on desktop
All drawers use AnimatePresence + motion.div from Framer Motion
Drawer backdrop click closes the drawer

Performance Rules

React.memo on: KanbanColumn, TaskCard, StickyNote, LogEntry
useMemo for: filtered/sorted task lists, canvas item transforms, chart data
useCallback for: drag handlers, form submit handlers passed as props
Lazy load page components with React.lazy + Suspense
Images (weather icons, avatar initials): always specify width and height

File Organization
api/          — one file per resource, typed return values
components/   — organized by feature domain (home/, productivity/, canvas/, diary/, ui/)
hooks/        — one hook per concern, prefixed with `use`
stores/       — uiStore.ts, canvasStore.ts only
types/        — index.ts only, never split
pages/        — one file per route

---
description: SQLite schema rules, query patterns, and migration conventions.
globs: ["backend/database/**", "backend/src/**Repository.php"]
alwaysApply: false
---
Database Rules
Schema Immutability

Never modify schema.sql directly after the first migration
All schema changes go in numbered migration files: migrations/001_add_column.sql, migrations/002_create_index.sql
migrate.php tracks applied migrations in a _migrations table
Production migrations must be reversible — include a -- DOWN section in each migration file

Query Patterns
Always Filter Soft Deletes
sql-- CORRECT
SELECT * FROM tasks WHERE project_id = ? AND deleted_at IS NULL
-- WRONG — never omit this
SELECT * FROM tasks WHERE project_id = ?
Fractional Display Order Queries
sql-- Get tasks for Kanban column ordered correctly
SELECT * FROM tasks
WHERE status = ? AND deleted_at IS NULL
ORDER BY display_order ASC, created_at ASC
Joining for Relations
sql-- Always LEFT JOIN — don't INNER JOIN relations that may be NULL
SELECT t.*, p.title AS project_title, p.color AS project_color
FROM tasks t
LEFT JOIN projects p ON t.project_id = p.id AND p.deleted_at IS NULL
WHERE t.id = ? AND t.deleted_at IS NULL
Pagination
sqlSELECT * FROM tasks WHERE deleted_at IS NULL
ORDER BY created_at DESC
LIMIT ? OFFSET ?
-- Always pair with a COUNT(*) query for total
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM tasks WHERE deleted_at IS NULL
Index Rules

Every foreign key column must have an index
Every column used in WHERE filters must have an index
Compound index for Kanban: (status, display_order)
Compound index for diary timeline: (logged_at DESC)
Never index columns that are only in SELECT — only WHERE/ORDER BY/JOIN columns

SQLite-Specific Gotchas

AUTOINCREMENT is slower than just INTEGER PRIMARY KEY — use the latter unless you need guaranteed non-reuse of IDs (we do not)
WAL mode must be set on every new connection — it's not persisted in the file header reliably
unixepoch() is the correct SQLite function for current Unix timestamp (not strftime('%s','now'))
Foreign key enforcement is OFF by default — always PRAGMA foreign_keys = ON
JSON columns are TEXT — SQLite has no native JSON type; validate structure in PHP before writing
Boolean columns: INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0 CHECK(col IN (0,1)) — never BOOLEAN type

Daily Snapshot Builder
SnapshotService::buildForDate(string $date) must:

Count tasks where due_date falls within the day and deleted_at IS NULL → tasks_planned
Count tasks where completed_at falls within the day → tasks_completed
Count tasks where created_at falls within the day → tasks_added
Count diary logs for the day → log_count
AVG mood/energy from diary logs for the day
UPSERT into daily_snapshots (INSERT OR REPLACE)
Run automatically at midnight via a cron job hitting POST /api/snapshots/build

---
description: REST API contract — request/response shapes, status codes, and frontend/backend sync rules.
globs: ["backend/src/Controllers/", "frontend/src/api/"]
alwaysApply: false
---
API Contract Rules
Response Envelope — Strict
Every response must be one of these two shapes:
typescript// Success
{ "success": true, "data": T, "meta"?: { "total": number, "page": number, "per_page": number } }

// Error
{ "success": false, "error": { "code": string, "message": string, "field"?: string } }
No exceptions. No bare arrays. No bare objects. No non-JSON responses (except 204 No Content for OPTIONS).
HTTP Status Codes
SituationCodeSuccessful GET / successful POST (non-creation)200Successful POST (created resource)201Successful DELETE (soft)200OPTIONS preflight204Validation error422Auth failure (bad/missing API key)401Resource not found404Method not allowed405Server / DB error500
Pagination

All list endpoints accept ?page=1&per_page=50
Default per_page: 50 for tasks/diary, 20 for AI plans, unlimited for goals/projects (they're always small)
Response includes meta.total, meta.page, meta.per_page
Frontend uses useInfiniteQuery for diary log feed, regular useQuery for everything else

Mutation DTOs — Frontend to Backend
The frontend sends only the DTO fields. The backend ignores any extra fields. Required vs optional:
CreateTaskDTO (POST /api/tasks):

Required: title (string, non-empty)
Optional: project_id, goal_id, parent_task_id, description, status (default: backlog), priority (default: 2), estimated_mins, due_date, canvas_x, canvas_y

KanbanReorderDTO (PATCH /api/tasks/reorder):

Required: moves array of { task_id: number, new_status: TaskStatus, new_display_order: number }
Process all moves in a single transaction

CreateDiaryLogDTO (POST /api/diary):

Required: body (string, non-empty)
Optional: log_type (default: activity), project_id, task_id, goal_id, mood_score, energy_score, duration_mins, logged_at (default: now)

Briefing Endpoint (GET /api/briefing)
Single aggregate endpoint for the Home Hub. Returns DailyBriefing:
{
  date, weather, events (today's calendar), emails (top 5 unread),
  tasks_today (due_date = today), tasks_overdue (due_date < today, not done),
  recent_logs (last 5), ai_plan (today's morning plan if exists), snapshot
}
All data fetched in parallel using PDO; weather/calendar/email from cache tables.
Total response time target: < 200ms on shared hosting.
Error Code Taxonomy
Predefined codes the frontend handles:

NOT_FOUND — resource doesn't exist or is soft-deleted
VALIDATION_ERROR — missing/invalid field (include field key)
UNAUTHORIZED — missing or invalid X-Codex-Key
DUPLICATE — unique constraint violation
EXTERNAL_API_ERROR — Google/OpenWeather/Anthropic call failed
QUOTA_EXCEEDED — Anthropic rate limit hit
DB_ERROR — SQLite write failure

Frontend API Module Pattern
Each frontend/src/api/*.ts file exports typed functions:
typescript// tasks.ts
export async function getTasks(filters: TaskFilters): Promise<ApiResponse<Task[]>> {
  const response = await client.get('/tasks', { params: filters });
  return response.data;
}

export async function createTask(dto: CreateTaskDTO): Promise<ApiResponse<Task>> {
  const response = await client.post('/tasks', dto);
  return response.data;
}
Never use fetch directly — always client (Axios instance from api/client.ts).
Never destructure .data inside the API module — let the hook/component handle the success check.

---
description: Anthropic API integration rules — prompt construction, response parsing, and cost controls.
globs: ["backend/src/Services/AnthropicService.php", "frontend/src/components/home/AiPlanCard.tsx", "frontend/src/hooks/useAiPlan.ts"]
alwaysApply: false
---
AI Integration Rules
Model
Always use claude-sonnet-4-20250514. Never hardcode any other model string. Read from settings if overridden, but validate against an allowlist.
Prompt Construction (AnthropicService.php)
System Prompt Template
You are a personal productivity coach for a single user's Life OS system.
Today is {date} ({day_of_week}). The user's work hours are {work_start}:00–{work_end}:00.
Weather: {temp}°C, {condition}.
Be concise, practical, and specific. Avoid generic advice.
User Prompt — Morning Plan
Here are my planned tasks for today:
{foreach task: "- [{priority_label}] {title} (est. {estimated_mins}min, project: {project_title})"}

Recent diary logs (last 24h):
{foreach log: "- [{log_type}] {body} ({duration_mins}min)"}

Today's calendar:
{foreach event: "- {title} {start_time}–{end_time}"}

Please provide a morning plan as JSON only. No markdown, no explanation outside the JSON.
Required structure:
{
  "parsed_schedule": [{"start_time": "HH:MM", "end_time": "HH:MM", "task_id": null|number, "task_title": "string", "notes": "string", "is_break": boolean}],
  "suggested_tasks": [{"task_id": number, "action": "defer|reschedule|prioritize|split|delegate|drop", "reason": "string"}],
  "reflection": "string (2-3 sentences max)",
  "score": number (1-100)
}
User Prompt — Evening Reflection
Same structure but focus on what was completed vs planned, energy pattern, and one key insight.
Response Parsing
php$raw = $response['content'][0]['text'];
// Strip any accidental markdown fences
$clean = preg_replace('/^```json\s*|\s*```$/m', '', trim($raw));
$parsed = json_decode($clean, true);
if (json_last_error() !== JSON_ERROR_NONE) {
    // Store raw_response for debugging, return partial result
    // Never throw — return what we have
}
Always store raw_response even if parsing fails. Log prompt_tokens and completion_tokens to ai_plans table for cost tracking.
Cost Controls

Rate limit AI plan generation: max 3 calls per day per plan_type
Check ai_plans table before generating: if a plan exists for today+type and force_regenerate is false, return cached
Truncate task list to max 20 tasks in prompt (prioritize by priority DESC, due_date ASC)
Truncate diary logs to last 10 entries in prompt
Max max_tokens: 1500 for morning/evening plans, 2000 for weekly

Frontend Plan Card (AiPlanCard.tsx)

Show loading skeleton during generation (can take 5-15 seconds)
Display schedule as a visual timeline (time blocks, color-coded by task priority)
"Suggested Tasks" shown as action chips — clicking one opens the task drawer
reflection text shown in a subtle card below the timeline
Score shown as a circular progress indicator (1-100)
"Regenerate" button calls POST /api/ai/plan/generate with force_regenerate: true; confirm dialog first (costs tokens)

---
description: Capacitor (mobile) and Tauri (desktop) integration rules, plus responsive design requirements.
globs: ["frontend/src//*.tsx", "capacitor.config.ts", "src-tauri/"]
alwaysApply: false
---
Mobile & Desktop Rules
Responsive Breakpoints (Tailwind)

base (0px+): mobile — single column, bottom nav, full-width components
md (768px+): tablet — two-column layouts appear, sidebar replaces bottom nav
lg (1024px+): desktop — full sidebar, multi-column dashboard grid
Never design for desktop first. Every component must be usable at 375px width.

Touch & Interaction

Minimum tap target: 44×44px (WCAG) — apply min-h-[44px] min-w-[44px] to all interactive elements
No hover-only affordances — anything on hover must also be accessible on long-press or secondary tap
Kanban drag-and-drop: use @dnd-kit pointer sensors (works for both mouse and touch)
Canvas workspace: use Pointer Events API (not Mouse Events) for pan/drag — enables touch support
Swipe gestures (diary log dismiss, task complete): implement with useSwipe hook using touchstart/touchend

Capacitor-Specific

Import native plugins only inside if (Capacitor.isNativePlatform()) guards
Haptic feedback on: task completion, quick log submit, drag-and-drop drop

ts  import { Haptics, ImpactStyle } from '@capacitor/haptics';
  await Haptics.impact({ style: ImpactStyle.Medium });

Pull-to-refresh on: Home Hub, Diary feed

ts  // Use @capacitor/push-notifications only after user explicitly enables in Settings

Deep links: codex:// scheme — configure in capacitor.config.ts
Status bar: dark content on light, light content on dark — set in App.tsx on mount
Safe area insets: use env(safe-area-inset-bottom) for bottom nav padding (iPhone notch)

css  padding-bottom: calc(env(safe-area-inset-bottom) + 16px);
Tauri-Specific

System tray: show unread task count badge
Global shortcut: Cmd/Ctrl+Shift+L opens QuickLogBar in a floating mini-window
Auto-launch: optional, user-controlled in Settings
Window size: remember last window size/position in Tauri store
File system access: SQLite path uses Tauri appDataDir() on desktop, not hardcoded path

AppShell Layout
tsx// Mobile: bottom nav tabs
<nav className="fixed bottom-0 left-0 right-0 flex h-16 items-center justify-around
                bg-codex-surface border-t border-codex-border
                pb-[env(safe-area-inset-bottom)] md:hidden">

// Desktop: left sidebar
<aside className="hidden md:flex md:w-16 lg:w-60 flex-col h-screen
                  bg-codex-surface border-r border-codex-border">
Network & Offline

TanStack Query's networkMode: 'offlineFirst' for all queries
Show offline banner when navigator.onLine === false
Diary QuickLogBar works offline: queue in IndexedDB, sync on reconnect (implement in Phase 2)
API base URL: VITE_API_URL env var — different values for dev/mobile/desktop builds

---
description: Testing conventions and what to test in Project Codex.
globs: ["backend/tests/", "frontend/src//.test.{ts,tsx}", "frontend/src/**/.spec.{ts,tsx}"]
alwaysApply: false
---
Testing Rules
What to Test (Prioritised)

PHP Repository methods — all SQL queries, filter combinations, soft delete, boolean casting
PHP API response envelopes — correct shape, correct status codes
TypeScript type guards — isApiSuccess(), enum validators
React hooks — useKanbanReorder, useQuickLog, useCanvasDrag
Utility functions — date formatting, fractional order calculation, prompt builder

What NOT to Test

Tailwind class names
Framer Motion animation values
Zustand store shape (covered by TypeScript)
External API responses (mock them, don't test the mocks)

PHP Testing (PHPUnit)

Test file mirrors source: src/Repositories/TaskRepository.php → tests/Repositories/TaskRepositoryTest.php
Use in-memory SQLite (:memory:) — run schema before each test, wipe after
Never test via HTTP in unit tests — test Repository and Service classes directly
Mock external services (AnthropicService, GoogleAuthService) with PHPUnit mocks

TypeScript Testing (Vitest)

Co-locate tests: hooks/useTasks.test.ts next to hooks/useTasks.ts
Mock TanStack Query with @tanstack/react-query test utilities
Mock Axios with vi.mock('../api/client')
Component tests use @testing-library/react — test behaviour not implementation

Test Data Factories
PHP:
php// tests/Factories/TaskFactory.php
TaskFactory::make(['status' => 'in_progress', 'project_id' => 1])
TaskFactory::makeMany(5, ['status' => 'backlog'])
TypeScript:
ts// tests/factories/task.ts
export const makeTask = (overrides: Partial<Task> = {}): Task => ({
  id: 1, title: 'Test task', status: 'backlog', priority: 2, ...overrides
})
